     Hello guys... Here I am writting for the first time in this 
article. I wanted to a few days ago, but I didn't feel (I think)
writting more than what I was doing for some line-routs (which 
are quite fast; I mean they could be of the best, but there still 
are some things to do). By the way, I've been learning some 3D
techniques (not filled, don't dream) for 2 or 3 days. As I have
not all the mathematical notions for it, I would have to study
those techniques to understand them well. In fact, Crystar of 
Pendragons gave me his ideas and techniques, I gave him my line-
routine (witch can draw about 13 lines of 320x200 each VBL), and
my optmisations. We just have done a 3D-line animation pretty 
fast but we don't have optimized the animation-techniques.
     Well. I was without my ST for about a month and a half, just
before the Convention. So I didn't really feel coding at the 
beginning. I had a screen to do, it isn't finished yet (I worked 
just for 2 days for it). It would be a fullscreen with hardware-
scroller of 256 lines height, with a Wizball-sprite of more than
200x200 (I can't remember), and, if possible, with digi-
soundtrack. And now only the scroller is done. The sprite is 
really terrible to optimise, and as I don't want to optimise it
bit by bit, I think I'll make a program to do it. The lone 
problem is in the fact that I really don't want to do it during 
the Convention. 
     I've seen some finished screens from Mister Bee, Adso, 

Pendragons, Ziggy Stardust... All are really good!! And what is 
terrific (at least, for me) is that some were done in the first 
days of the Convention! That means, I don't feel coding many 
hours a day, so I haven't (for now) a large productivity, I just 
hope to code faster when I'll be back.
     Now stop writting about my life!
The Convention is really (that means R-E-A-L-L-Y) cool, 
delirious! Sometimes there are some water-huntings, where 
every guy goes down in the washtub. And, as I have (once again)
taken precautions, I brought my camera, and managed to take 
photos of everyone (even of me!!) in the water. Well, I just say 
that it was a really good idea to make everyone going into the 
watertub!!     Perhaps in a future screen, you will see some of 
those cliches...
     Okay. I saw that Dogue made a very big logo. No problem.
