-------------- DOGUE DE MAUVE from OVERLANDERS ----------- 05.00 PM
 
Yes, it's me again, at the same hour... Well, in fact, we're now 
28/08/90! We had a very turbulent night, in fact. We first 
watched BEETLEJUICE, a very nice & delirious film by Tim BURTON 
then we had good time with ROBOCOP, great film, too. Of course, 
since I remain as serious and as reasonnable as you know, I 
decided to go to bed. Unfortunately, the PENDRAGONS had to pack
their luggages (with Huffman algorythm!) and they disturbed me by 
putting the light on and walking through the attic. A few minutes 
later, a few guys came, intending to disturb the PENDRAGONS. The 
whole attic was quickly filled by some crazy shouting barbarians 
fighting eachothers. Pillows, sleepbags and mattress were flying 
through the air. I desesperately tried to calm everybody but they 
didn't want to stop. I finally had to fight them myself, using my 
"FORCE MAUVE" suit (in fact, my mauve sleepbag) and all my tired 
power... Four or five guys tried to catch me, intending to tickle 
me. I resisted and three of them are now in hospital...
That was really tiresome! When we finally stopped this terrible 
war, it was 4.45 AM and the PENDRAGONS had to get up at 6.00 AM 
and leave at 8.00 AM. Of course, these stupid boys didn't try to 
be discreet. They took a big cooking-pot and drummed against it 
like mad musicians. An AWFUL noise!!! They even managed to damage 
the pot!!! Dumb brains!!!
In fact, it's a pity that they left us. These guys are very cool, 
actually. They are our best friends in France (they aren't 
pretentious, nor jealous; they're good coders and very pleasant
and funny boys).
OK, let's talk about the present time. Most of us are now playing 
various games ("TECH" on AMIGA -a kind of TRON-, "CHAOS STRIKES 
BACK" on ST -a kind of Shoot'em up-, "SUPER SPRINT" on ST -a sort 
of mindboggling game- and "QUARTZ" -a very nice adventure game I 
played a few minutes before-).
This no more a coding-party but a playing-party. I must say we 
all worked quite hard (I even programmed ASSEMBLER! Yes, 
ASSEMBLER!!!) and we now need to rest a bit... 
Well, FURYO needs his "SUPER SPRINT" dose or he will die. I'll 
stop 'coz I don't want to be considered as a murderer.

                                                        "See" ya!
                                                    DDM (5.40 PM)

------------------ Ziggy STARDUST from OVERLANDERS ------------- 00.00 PM

Ok! For the first time, and surely the last, I write in this 
article. I didn't write before because I was too busy! Not busy to 
code anything, but to play to various game. I stop now, because 
it's too easy, I always win! Ha ha ha!! It's really hard to code 
here, because every member make some "music-war", which means that 
they try to put the volume of their ST at the maximum. The result 
is that I even can't hear myself thinking. Well, in fact, it's 
not a bad thing, because I feel very lazy, those last time. WE 
ARE ON HOLIDAY!!! Well, in fact, not for a long time. GGGRRR! 
Don't laugh, Adso, that's not funny! (He goes back to school just 
in more than one month!). With Humungus, I'v done some pretty 
nice 3D forms animations. It's very funny! I want make rebound every 
object, even the car and the space craft. I don't understand  
why, Humungus does not agree with this movement.

Arf arf!!! Pib has just been thrown to the washtub! Poor little 
guy! It's very cold, because we are in moutains, at 1200 meters 
high! I've already be thrown in the wasthub two time. Well, I 
must say that this convention is completly delirious, sleeping 
here is very difficult! Anyway, it seems that more I sleep, more 
I'm tired. The only thing I've done here, is including the line 
rout of Dim in my filled vector routs, and now, my routs are 
completly bugged! Arrrg! I have no .BAK!! Ok, bye everybody! We 
come back home in two days.

