------- DOGUE DE MAUVE from OVERLANDERS ------- 18.47 PM (31/9/90)

Yeah! I'm back in town (I mean in ASNIERES, were I live) and I'm 
supposed to tell you what we did the last two days. The 
convention ended the 29/9/90. In the morning, we received a 
journalist who wanted to know what we were doing and perhaps make 
an article about our convention. We showed him our last demos & 
game previews and explained who we were and what we were doing 
here. He took a few pictures from us, too. Well, let's hope we'll 
be able to get this article quickly...
Just before leaving, a few guys were thrown in the washtub again 
(good luck that it was hot). Then, two pretty taxi-girls came to 
drive us to the station (all the others seemed to find this women 
wonderful but I thought they were not that beautiful in fact).

After the convention, we (I, HUMUNGUS, ADSO, GUDUL, LUDUG, ZIGGY, 
FURYO & STAN MERCURY) decided to go to the AQUA-SOMETHING (a kind 
of giant swimming-pool with jaccuzi, "waving pool", fountains, 
hot "bubbling" water and so on... We even had great time in a 140 
meters high toboggan (nearly all, 'coz STAN was frightened and 
HUMUNGUS didn't want to loose his lenses). Great, actually, 
especially when I loose my "swimming carpet", heard FURYO 
shouting 10 meters behind me in the tunnel and had to hurry to 
avoid a terrible crush (he's quite a big guy, you know!).
A very funny afternoon!
But we had to leave in the evening... OVERLANDERS go home!

I would like to thanx and congratulate again FURYO & STAN MERCURY 
who organized this great "BEACH PARTY" (where's the beach?). A 
special thought for STAN who's leaving for army...
Thanx to all inhabitants in the village and to STAN's and FURYO's 
parents who accomodated us very kindly.

That's all for this time. 
                                                 "See" you soon &
                                       May the MAUVE be with you!

